(# Q2.1 Infrastructure Requirements Table) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document records the live Chameleon evidence used to right-size the Q2 DevOps/Platform deployment for ChefMate.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Deployment Snapshot) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Site: `KVM@TACC`) Tj
T*
(- Cluster: `3`-node `k3s` cluster) Tj
T*
(- Node capacity: lease-backed `m1.large` equivalent capacity, `4 vCPU`, `8 GiB RAM`, `40 GiB disk` per node) Tj
T*
(- Healthy namespaces observed: `chefmate-platform`, `chefmate-staging`) Tj
T*
(- Bound PVCs observed:) Tj
T*
(  - `minio-pvc` = `20Gi`) Tj
T*
(  - `postgres-pvc` = `10Gi`) Tj
T*
(  - `mealie-data-pvc` = `8Gi`) Tj
T*
(  - `mealie-postgres-pvc` = `8Gi`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Infrastructure Requirements Table) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Service | Namespace | GPU | CPU req/limit | Mem req/limit | Chameleon evidence | Right-sizing rationale |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| `mealie` | `chefmate-staging` | `0 / 0` | `250m / 1000m` | `512Mi / 1Gi` | Healthy on `node1`; `kubectl top pods -A` showed) Tj
T*
(about `266Mi` RAM during live validation. | Light web app for milestone-scale traffic; request is about 2x observed steady-state) Tj
T*
(memory and limit leaves burst headroom. |) Tj
T*
(| `mealie-postgres` | `chefmate-staging` | `0 / 0` | `250m / 1000m` | `512Mi / 1Gi` | Healthy on `node3`; `mealie-postgres-pvc`) Tj
T*
(bound at `8Gi`. | Small durable database for Mealie only; conservative allocation relative to `4 vCPU / 8 GiB` node capacity. |) Tj
T*
(| `postgres` | `chefmate-platform` | `0 / 0` | `250m / 1000m` | `512Mi / 1Gi` | Healthy on `node2`; `postgres-pvc` bound at) Tj
T*
(`10Gi`. | MLflow metadata backend with modest Q2 load; small guaranteed share plus enough limit headroom for spikes. |) Tj
T*
(| `minio` | `chefmate-platform` | `0 / 0` | `250m / 1000m` | `512Mi / 1Gi` | Healthy on `node2`; `minio-pvc` bound at `20Gi`;) Tj
T*
(bucket-init job completed. | Small object store for MLflow artifacts; modest request is enough for steady use and `1Gi` covers) Tj
T*
(startup and small transfer bursts. |) Tj
T*
(| `mlflow` | `chefmate-platform` | `0 / 0` | `250m / 1000m` | `512Mi / 1Gi` | Healthy on `node3`; service exposed on port `8000`.) Tj
T*
(| Light UI/API workload for a small team; low request preserves cluster headroom while the limit supports interactive use. |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Why These Numbers Are Reasonable) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The chosen requests and limits are intentionally small relative to the leased node capacity:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- `250m` CPU request is about `6.25%` of a `4 vCPU` node) Tj
T*
(- `1000m` CPU limit is about `25%` of a `4 vCPU` node) Tj
T*
(- `512Mi` memory request is about `6.25%` of an `8 GiB` node) Tj
T*
(- `1Gi` memory limit is about `12.5%` of an `8 GiB` node) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This leaves substantial headroom for Kubernetes system services, storage provisioning, and startup bursts while still reserving) Tj
T*
(enough capacity for stable operation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Live Evidence Captured On Chameleon) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
